Java 8 introduced several powerful features that significantly improved the language, 
  especially in terms of functional programming, concurrency, and API enhancements.

  The major features in java 8:
=> Lambda Expression : Enables user to treat functionality as a method argument(functions as data).
=> Stream Api :A new way to process collections in a functional style. Supports operations like filter,map,reduce etc
=> Functional Interface :Interface with a single abstract method.
=> Default Methods : Interface methods with default implementation
=> Method References : shorthand for lambda expressions.
=> optional class: null-safe container class.
=> Date and Time api : Improved date and time handling
=> Nashorn Javascript Engine : Allows user to run javascript within java using javax.script.ScriptEngine
